%2C%20immediate%20policy%20considerations%20necessitate%20a%20nuanced%20approach.%20The%20establishment%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finterstatecouncil.gov.in%2Fpunchhi-commission%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJustice%20Madan%20Mohan%20Punchhi%20Commission%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202007%20underscores%20the%20need%20to%20address%20evolving%20challenges%20in%20the%20relationship%20between%20Central%20and%20state%20entities%2C%20rooted%20in%20shifts%20within%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20and%20economic%20landscape.%20In%20navigating%20these%20complexities%2C%20thoughtful%20analysis%20and%20an%20understanding%20of%20the%20fundamental%20reasons%20behind%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20limited%20discretionary%20powers%20are%20essential%20for%20informed%20reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20provisions%20in%20question%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20several%20constitutional%20provisions%20that%20raise%20concerns%20about%20the%20role%20of%20governors%20in%20India.%20Key%20articles%2C%20such%20as%20Article%20156%20that%20states%20that%20the%20governor%20shall%20hold%20office%20during%20the%20pleasure%20of%20the%20President%3B%20Article%20161%20that%20gives%20the%20governor%20the%20power%20to%20grant%20pardons%2C%20reprieves%2C%20etc.%3B%20Article%20163%20that%20gives%20the%20governor%20discretionary%20powers%20of%20appointment%20of%20a%20chief%20minister%20when%20no%20party%20has%20a%20clear%20majority%20in%20the%20state%20legislature%2C%20powers%20in%20times%20of%20no-confidence%20motions%20and%20powers%20in%20case%20of%20the%20failure%20of%20constitutional%20machinery%20in%20the%20state%3B%20Article%20200%20that%20gives%20the%20governor%20the%20power%20to%20give%20assent%2C%20withhold%20assent%2C%20or%20reserve%20the%20bill%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20President%20passed%20by%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%3B%20Article%20356%20that%20gives%20powers%20to%20the%20governor%20to%20dismiss%20the%20assembly%20in%20case%20of%20the%20failure%20of%20constitutional%20machinery%20in%20the%20State%3B%20Article%20361%20that%20makes%20the%20governor%20not%20answerable%20to%20any%20court%20for%20the%20exercise%20and%20performance%20of%20his%20powers%20and%20duties%20and%20the%20very%20manner%20of%20the%20appointment%20of%20the%20governors%20%E2%80%93%20are%20some%20of%20the%20discretionary%20powers%20that%20are%20in%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20underscored%20that%20these%20powers%20should%20ideally%20be%20exercised%20in%20consultation%20with%20state%20governments%2C%20the%20provision%20exempting%20governors%20from%20court%20accountability%20raises%20questions%20about%20the%20balance%20of%20authority.%20The%20increasing%20trend%20of%20political%20class%20appointments%20made%20by%20the%20President%20on%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20ruling%20dispensation%20at%20the%20Centre%20further%20amplifies%20worries%20about%20potential%20Central%20influence.%20Henceforth%2C%20it%20is%20imperative%20to%20reassess%20and%20recalibrate%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20powers%2C%20ensuring%20a%20more%20democratic%20and%20transparent%20appointment%20process%20in%20harmony%20with%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20federal%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovernors-as-ruling-partys-storm-troopers%5C%22%3EGovernors%20as%20Ruling%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Storm%20Troopers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlternative%20framework%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevamping%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20role%20demands%20a%20nuanced%20policy%20overhaul%2C%20particularly%20in%20addressing%20the%20pivotal%20matters%20of%20gubernatorial%20appointments.%20This%20proposed%20framework%20advocates%20for%20a%20collaborative%20process%20between%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20states%20to%20ensure%20transparency%20and%20open%20communication%20channels.%20Emphasising%20the%20governor%20as%20a%20mediator%20rather%20than%20a%20mere%20agent%20of%20the%20Centre%2C%20the%20suggestion%20is%20to%20adopt%20a%20selection%20method%20akin%20to%20that%20of%20the%20President%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20involves%20an%20electoral%20college%20comprising%20elected%20members%20of%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20and%20representatives%20from%20all%20panchayat%2Fmunicipality%20wards%20of%20the%20state%2C%20excluding%20legislative%20council%2Fnominated%20members%2C%20if%20any.%20Such%20an%20approach%20offers%20a%20more%20balanced%20and%20independent%20selection%20process%2C%20steering%20clear%20of%20undue%20influence%20from%20either%20the%20Centre%20or%20the%20state%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20essential%20facet%20requiring%20attention%20lies%20in%20deterring%20the%20political%20class%20from%20viewing%20governorship%20as%20a%20mid-career%20alternative.%20To%20address%20this%20concern%2C%20it%20is%20crucial%20to%20implement%20policies%20that%20disqualify%20governors%20from%20seeking%20any%20subsequent%20public%20office.%20Drawing%20inspiration%20from%20the%20model%20followed%20for%20the%20President%20of%20India%2C%20governors%20should%20be%20ineligible%20for%20appointments%20to%20other%20public%20positions%2C%20restricting%20their%20scope%20to%20the%20role%20of%20governor%20or%20elevated%20offices%20such%20as%20the%20President%20or%20Vice-President.%20Such%20measures%20are%20pivotal%20in%20curbing%20the%20influx%20of%20people%20from%20political%20parties%2C%20with%20individual%20interests%20to%20further%20their%20political%20ambitions%2C%20from%20taking%20the%20public%20office%20of%20the%20Governor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20that%20comes%20up%20next%20is%20regarding%20the%20resignation%20and%20impeachment%20of%20the%20governor.%20Empowering%20legislatures%20to%20impeach%20governors%20in%20cases%20of%20constitutional%20deficiencies%20would%20enhance%20accountability.%20The%20impeachment%20procedure%20of%20the%20governor%20must%20be%20made%20such%20that%20the%20respective%20legislative%20assembly%20of%20the%20state%20can%20initiate%20an%20impeachment%20process%20and%20impeach%20the%20governor%20by%20a%20two-third%20vote.%20The%20governor%20may%2C%20other%20than%20to%20the%20President%20of%20India%2C%20submit%20his%20resignation%20to%20the%20Assembly%20Speaker.%20Another%20revision%20needed%20in%20this%20context%20is%20on%20fixing%20a%20tenure%20limit%20of%20five%20years%20upon%20the%20governor.%20Until%20now%2C%20the%20appointment%20has%20been%20initiated%20and%20sustained%20at%20the%20pleasure%20of%20the%20President.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20must%20have%20jurisdiction%20upon%20the%20duties%20and%20powers%20exercised%20by%20the%20governor.%20This%20makes%20any%20overriding%20exercise%20of%20powers%20by%20the%20Governor%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20governor%20can%20work%20in%20harmony%20with%20the%20President%20of%20India%20and%20can%20act%20in%20an%20independent%20manner%2C%20devoid%20of%20any%20vested%20interest%20or%20political%20opinions%2C%20only%20if%20such%20changes%20to%20the%20constitutional%20role%20of%20the%20governor%20are%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EYadul%20Krishna%20is%20the%20Parliamentary%20Secretary%20to%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20Binoy%20Viswam.%20Views%20expressed%20are%20personal.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700189005000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F27102504%2FKolkata%25E2%2580%2599s-Raj-Bhavan-could-be-worth-almost-Rs-2000-crores-today-FB-1200x700-compressed.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fabolishing-governors-post-isnt-a-good-idea-whats-needed-is-a-rethink%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20valid%20criticisms%20regarding%20the%20potential%20overreach%20of%20gubernatorial%20powers%20deserve%20attention%2C%20it%20is%20crucial%20to%20appreciate%20the%20intricate%20and%20significant%20role%20governors%20play%20in%20upholding%20the%20constitutional%20fabric.%22%2