es%20risk%20weights%20for%20personal%20loans%20and%20credit%20cards%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700157251000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-12%2F12%2Ffull%2F1670867067-1709.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fbanking%2Frbi-tightens-norms-increases-risk-weights-for-personal-loan-credit-cards-123111601200_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Loans%20likely%20to%20become%20dearer%3B%20marginal%20impact%20on%20bank's%20capital%20adequacy%20ratio%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fbanking%2Frbi-tightens-norms-increases-risk-weights-for-personal-loan-credit-cards-123111601200_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findustry%2Fbanking%2Frbi-tightens-norms-increases-risk-weights-for-personal-loan-credit-cards-123111601200_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findustry%2Fbanking%2Frbi-tightens-norms-increases-risk-weights-for-personal-loan-credit-cards-123111601200_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20An%20Indian%20Startup%20Hacked%20The%20World%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EChuck%20Randall%20was%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20unveiling%20an%20ambitious%20real%20estate%20deal%20he%20hoped%20would%20give%20his%20small%20Native%20American%20tribe%20a%20bigger%20cut%20of%20a%20potentially%20lucrative%20casino%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20well-timed%20leak%20derailed%20it%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%20of%202012%2C%20printed%20excerpts%20from%20Randall's%20private%20emails%20were%20hand-distributed%20across%20the%20Shinnecock%20Nation's%20square-mile%20reservation%2C%20a%20wooded%20peninsula%20hanging%20off%20the%20South%20Fork%20of%20Long%20Island.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20five-page%20pamphlets%20detailed%20secret%20negotiations%20between%20Randall%2C%20his%20tribal%20government%20allies%20and%20outside%20investors%20to%20wrest%20some%20of%20the%20profits%20from%20the%20tribe's%20then-partner%20in%20the%20gambling%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20sparked%20an%20uproar.%20The%20pamphlets%20claimed%20Randall's%20plan%20would%20sell%20out%20the%20tribe's%20%E2%80%9CLANDS%2C%20RESOURCES%2C%20and%20FUTURE%20REVENUES.%E2%80%9D%20Within%20days%2C%20four%20of%20Randall's%20allies%20were%20voted%20out%20of%20tribal%20government.%20Randall%2C%20who%20held%20no%20formal%20position%20with%20the%20tribe%2C%20was%20ordered%20to%20cease%20acting%20on%20its%20behalf.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20upheaval%2C%20the%20Shinnecocks'%20casino%20hopes%20faded.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20lost%20the%20biggest%20economic%20opportunity%20that%20has%20come%20to%20the%20tribe%20in%20forever%2C%E2%80%9D%20Randall%20told%20Reuters.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20emails%20were%20weaponized.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scandal%20that%20roiled%20the%20Shinnecocks%20barely%20registered%20beyond%20the%20reservation.%20But%20it%20was%20part%20of%20a%20phenomenon%20that%20has%20drawn%20interest%20from%20law%20enforcement%20and%20intelligence%20agencies%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20Atlantic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERandall's%20inbox%20was%20breached%20by%20a%20New%20Delhi-based%20information%20technology%20firm%20named%20Appin%2C%20whose%20sudden%20interference%20in%20the%20matters%20of%20a%20faraway%20tribe%20was%20part%20of%20a%20sprawling%20cyber-mercenary%20operation%20that%20extended%20across%20the%20world%2C%20a%20Reuters%20investigation%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20company%20hacked%20on%20an%20industrial%20scale%2C%20stealing%20data%20from%20political%20leaders%2C%20international%20executives%2C%20prominent%20attorneys%20and%20more.%20By%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Shinnecock%20scandal%2C%20Appin%20was%20a%20premier%20provider%20of%20cyberespionage%20services%20for%20private%20investigators%20working%20on%20behalf%20of%20big%20business%2C%20law%20firms%20and%20wealthy%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnauthorized%20access%20to%20computer%20systems%20is%20a%20crime%20worldwide%2C%20including%20in%20India.%20Yet%20at%20least%2017%20pitch%20documents%20prepared%20for%20prospective%20business%20partners%20and%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters%20advertised%20Appin's%20prowess%20in%20activities%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Ccyber%20spying%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9Cemail%20monitoring%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9Ccyber%20warfare%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csocial%20engineering%2C%E2%80%9D%20security%20lingo%20for%20manipulating%20people%20into%20revealing%20sensitive%20information.%20In%20one%202010%20presentation%2C%20the%20company%20explicitly%20bragged%20about%20hacking%20businessmen%20on%20behalf%20of%20corporate%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20previously%20named%20Appin%20in%20a%20story%20about%20Indian%20cyber%20mercenaries%20published%20last%20year.%20Other%20media%20outlets%20%E2%80%93%20including%20The%20New%20Yorker%2C%20Paris-based%20Intelligence%20Online%2C%20Swiss%20investigative%20program%20Rundschau%20and%20tech%20companies%20such%20as%20Alphabet-owned%20Google%E2%80%93%20have%20also%20reported%20on%20the%20firm's%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20report%20paints%20the%20clearest%20picture%20yet%20of%20how%20Appin%20operated%2C%20detailing%20the%20world-spanning%20extent%20of%20its%20business%2C%20and%20international%20law%20enforcement's%20abortive%20efforts%20to%20get%20a%20handle%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERun%20by%20a%20pair%20of%20brothers%2C%20Rajat%20and%20Anuj%20Khare%2C%20the%20company%20began%20as%20a%20small%20Indian%20educational%20startup.%20It%20went%20on%20to%20train%20a%20generation%20of%20spies%20for%20hire%20that%20are%20still%20in%20business%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20cyber%20defense%20training%20organizations%20in%20India%20carry%20the%20Appin%20name%2C%20the%20legacy%20of%20an%20old%20franchise%20model.%20But%20there's%20no%20suggestion%20that%20those%20firms%20are%20involved%20in%20hacking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20company%20hacked%20on%20an%20industrial%20scale%2C%20stealing%20data%20from%20political%20leaders%2C%20international%20executives%2C%20sports%20figures%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajat%20Khare's%20U.S.%20representative%2C%20the%20law%20firm%20Clare%20Locke%2C%20rejected%20any%20association%20between%20its%20client%20and%20the%20cyber-mercenary%20business.%20It%20said%20Khare%20%E2%80%9Chas%20never%20operated%20or%20supported%2C%20and%20certainly%20did%20not%20create%2C%20any%20illegal%20%E2%80%98hack%20for%20hire'%20industry%20in%20India%20or%20anywhere%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20series%20of%20letters%20sent%20to%20Reuters%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20Clare%20Locke%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CMr.%20Khare%20has%20dedicated%20much%20of%20his%20career%20to%20the%20fields%20of%20information%20technology%20security%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20cyber-defense%20and%20the%20prevention%20of%20illicit%20hacking.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClare%20Locke%20said%20that%2C%20under%20Khare's%20tenure%2C%20Appin%20specialized%20in%20training%20thousands%20of%20students%20in%20cybersecurity%2C%20robotics%20and%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20%E2%80%9Cnever%20in%20illicit%20hacking.%E2%80%9D%20The%20lawyers%20said%20Khare%20left%20Appin%2C%20in%20part%2C%20because%20rogue%20actors%20were%20operating%20under%20the%20company's%20brand%2C%20and%20he%20wanted%20%E2%80%9Cto%20avoid%20the%20appearance%20of%20associations%20with%20people%20who%20were%20misusing%20the%20Appin%20name.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyers%20described%20media%20articles%20tying%20Khare%20to%20hacking%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cfundamentally%20flawed.%E2%80%9D%20As%20for%20the%202010%20Appin%20presentation%20boasting%20of%20hacking%20services%2C%20they%20said%20Khare%20had%20never%20seen%20it%20before.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20document%20is%20a%20forgery%20or%20was%20doctored%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClare%20Locke%20added%20that%20Khare%20could%20not%20be%20held%20responsible%20for%20Appin%20employees%20who%20went%20on%20to%20work%20as%20mercenary%20hackers%2C%20saying%20that%20doing%20so%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20be%20akin%20to%20holding%20Harvard%20University%20responsible%20for%20the%20terrorist%20bombings%20carried%20out%20by%20its%20former%20student%20Ted%20Kaczynski%2C%E2%80%9D%20referring%20to%20the%20former%20math%20prodigy%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CUnabomber.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lawyer%20acting%20for%20Rajat's%20brother%2C%20Anuj%2C%20said%20his%20client's%20position%20was%20the%20same%20as%20the%20one%20laid%20out%20by%20Clare%20Locke.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20report%20on%20Appin%20draws%20on%20thousands%20of%20company%20emails%20as%20well%20as%20financial%20records%2C%20presentations%2C%20photos%20and%20instant%20messages%20from%20the%20firm.%20Reporters%20also%20reviewed%20case%20files%20from%20American%2C%20Norwegian%2C%20Dominican%20and%20Swiss%20law%20enforcement%2C%20and%20interviewed%20dozens%20of%20former%20Appin%20employees%20and%20hundreds%20of%20victims%20of%20India-based%20hackers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20gathered%20the%20material%20%E2%80%93%20which%20spans%202005%20until%20earlier%20this%20year%20%E2%80%93%20from%20ex-employees%2C%20clients%20and%20security%20professionals%20who've%20studied%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20verified%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20Appin%20communications%20with%2015%20people%2C%20including%20private%20investigators%20who%20commissioned%20hacks%20and%20ex-Appin%20hackers%20themselves.%20The%20news%20agency%20also%20asked%20U.S.%20cybersecurity%20firm%20SentinelOne%20to%20review%20the%20material%20for%20signs%20that%20it%20had%20been%20digitally%20altered.%20The%20firm%20said%20it%20found%20none.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20assess%20the%20emails%20to%20be%20accurately%20represented%20and%20verifiably%20associated%20with%20the%20Appin%20organization%2C%E2%80%9D%20SentinelOne%20researcher%20Tom%20Hegel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Khare's%20lawyers%20say%20Appin%20%E2%80%9Cfocused%20on%20teaching%20cybersecurity%20and%20cyber-defense%2C%E2%80%9D%20company%20communications%20seen%20by%20Reuters%20detailed%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20arsenal%20of%20hacking%20tools%2C%20including%20malicious%20code%20and%20websites.%20Hegel%20and%20two%20other%20U.S.-based%20researchers%20%E2%80%93%20one%20from%20cybersecurity%20firm%20Mandiant%2C%20the%20other%20from%20Symantec%20%E2%80%93%20all%20working%20independently%2C%20were%20able%20to%20match%20that%20infrastructure%20to%20publicly%20known%20cyberespionage%20campaigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20all%20lines%20up%20perfectly%2C%E2%80%9D%20Hegel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20Google%20saw%20hackers%20linked%20to%20Appin%20target%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20email%20accounts%20on%20its%20service%20alone%2C%20according%20to%20Shane%20Huntley%2C%20who%20leads%20the%20California%20company's%20cyber%20threat%20intelligence%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20groups%20worked%20very%20high%20volumes%2C%20to%20the%20point%20that%20we%20actually%20had%20to%20expand%20our%20systems%20and%20procedures%20to%20work%20out%20how%20to%20track%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20Huntley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20Appin%20has%20now%20largely%20disappeared%20from%20public%20view%2C%20but%20its%20impact%20is%20still%20felt%20today.%20Copycat%20firms%20led%20by%20Appin%20alumni%20continue%20to%20target%20thousands%2C%20according%20to%20court%20records%20and%20cybersecurity%20industry%20reporting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20were%20groundbreaking%2C%E2%80%9D%20Google's%20Huntley%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20companies%20at%20the%20moment%20who%20are%20picking%20up%20the%20baton%2C%20many%20of%20them%20are%20led%20by%20ex-employees%E2%80%9D%20of%20Appin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Get%20me%20result%20ASAP!!!'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrivate%20eyes%20have%20been%20hiring%20hackers%20to%20do%20their%20dirty%20work%20since%20the%20dawn%20of%20the%20internet.%20Former%20clients%20say%20Appin's%20central%20innovation%20was%20turning%20the%20cloak-and-dagger%20market%20into%20something%20more%20like%20an%20e-commerce%20platform%20for%20spy%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mercenaries%20marketed%20a%20digital%20dashboard%20with%20a%20menu%20of%20options%20for%20breaking%20into%20inboxes%2C%20including%20sending%20fake%2C%20booby-trapped%20job%20opportunities%2C%20bogus%20bribe%20offers%20and%20risqu%C3%A9%20messages%20with%20subject%20lines%20like%20%E2%80%9CMy%20Sister's%20Hot%20Friend.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECustomers%20would%20log%20in%20to%20a%20discreet%20site%20%E2%80%93%20once%20dubbed%20%E2%80%9CMy%20Commando%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20and%20ask%20Appin%20to%20break%20into%20emails%2C%20computers%20or%20phones.%20Users%20could%20follow%20the%20spies'%20progress%20as%20if%20they%20were%20tracking%20a%20delivery%2C%20eventually%20receiving%20instructions%20to%20download%20their%20victim's%20data%20from%20digital%20dead%20drops%2C%20according%20to%20logs%20of%20the%20system%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20best-organized%20system%20that%20I%20have%20ever%20seen%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Jochi%20G%C3%B3mez%2C%20a%20former%20news%20publisher%20in%20the%20Dominican%20Republic.%20G%C3%B3mez%20told%20Reuters%20that%20in%202011%20he%20paid%20Appin%20%245%2C000%20to%20%2410%2C000%20a%20month%20to%20spy%20on%20the%20Caribbean%20nation's%20elite%20and%20mine%20the%20material%20for%20stories%20for%20his%20now-defunct%20digital%20newspaper%2C%20El%20Siglo%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Appin's%20selling%20points%20was%20a%20project%20management%20tool%20once%20called%20%E2%80%9CMy%20Commando.%E2%80%9D%20Appin%20told%20customers%20it%20used%20the%20tool%20to%20tailor%20its%20hacking%20attempts%2C%20enticing%20targets%20with%20bogus%20business%20proposals%2C%20fake%20interview%20requests%20or%20porn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20booby-trapped%20emails%20were%20elaborate%20deceptions%2C%20like%20this%20message%20created%20in%20the%20name%20of%20a%20non-existent%20journalist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20relied%20on%20sex%20appeal%2C%20like%20this%20message%20promising%20photos%20of%20a%20woman%20taking%20off%20a%20traditional%20Indian%20dress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETargets%20who%20clicked%20would%20soon%20have%20their%20emails%20stolen%20by%20Appin%20%E2%80%93%20and%20read%20by%20the%20hackers'%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20reviewed%20more%20than%20a%20year's%20worth%20of%20activity%20from%20Appin's%20%E2%80%9CMy%20Commando%E2%80%9D%20system.%20The%20logs%20showed%20that%20G%C3%B3mez%20was%20one%20of%2070%20clients%2C%20mostly%20private%20investigators%2C%20from%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Britain%2C%20Switzerland%20and%20beyond%20who%20sought%20Appin's%20help%20in%20hacking%20hundreds%20of%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20marks%20were%20high-society%20figures%2C%20including%20a%20top%20New%20York%20art%20dealer%20and%20a%20French%20diamond%20heiress%2C%20according%20to%20the%20logs.%20Others%20were%20less%20prominent%2C%20like%20a%20New%20Jersey%20landscape%20architect%20suspected%20of%20having%20an%20affair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20detectives%20used%20the%20service%20frequently%2C%20among%20them%20Israeli%20private%20eye%20Aviram%20Halevi%2C%20who%20tasked%20the%20spies%20with%20going%20after%20at%20least%20three%20dozen%20people%20via%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20returning%20customer%20who%20needs%20the%20following%20addresses%20cracked%20ASAP%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20logs%20show%20Halevi%20telling%20the%20hackers%20in%20August%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20previously%20reported%20that%20Halevi%2C%20a%20former%20lieutenant%20colonel%20in%20the%20Israeli%20Defense%20Forces%2C%20hired%20Appin%20to%20spy%20on%20a%20litigant%20in%20a%20lawsuit%20in%20Israel%20on%20behalf%20of%20a%20client%20on%20the%20opposing%20side%20of%20the%20case.%20Halevi%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20questions%20about%20his%20ties%20to%20the%20hackers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20big%20user%20of%20My%20Commando%20was%20Israeli%20private%20detective%20Tamir%20Mor%2C%20who%20used%20the%20service%20around%20the%20same%20time%20to%20order%20hacks%20on%20more%20than%2040%20targets%2C%20the%20logs%20show.%20Among%20them%20were%20the%20late%20Russian%20oligarch%20Boris%20Berezovsky%20and%20Malaysian%20politician%20Mohamed%20Azmin%20Ali.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPlease%20get%20me%20result%20ASAP!!!%E2%80%9D%20Mor%20wrote%20on%20the%20My%20Commando%20chat%20feature%20after%20providing%20Appin%20with%20details%20about%20two%20members%20of%20Berezovsky's%20legal%20team%20in%20December%202011%2C%20the%20logs%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20could%20not%20establish%20Mor's%20motives%20for%20targeting%20Berezovsky%20and%20Azmin%2C%20whether%20he%20succeeded%20in%20hacking%20either%20of%20them%2C%20or%20on%20whose%20behalf%20he%20was%20working.%20Mor%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAzmin%2C%20a%20former%20cabinet%20minister%2C%20was%20a%20prominent%20opposition%20leader%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20hack%20attempts.%20He%20and%20his%20former%20party%20didn't%20respond%20to%20messages%20seeking%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20to%20hack%20Berezovsky%20came%20while%20the%20tycoon%20was%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20British%20court%20battle%20against%20fellow%20oligarch%20Roman%20Abramovich%20over%20the%20sale%20of%20a%20Russian%20oil%20company.%20The%20multibillion%20dollar%20case%20ended%20in%20a%20decisive%20defeat%20for%20Berezovsky.%20The%2067-year-old%20was%20found%20dead%20at%20his%20suburban%20English%20home%20the%20following%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMark%20Hastings%2C%20one%20of%20the%20Berezovsky%20lawyers%20mentioned%20in%20the%20My%20Commando%20logs%2C%20said%20he%20was%20not%20aware%20that%20he%20had%20been%20in%20Appin's%20crosshairs%2C%20but%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20entirely%20surprised.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20an%20open%20secret%20that%20lawyers%20are%20often%20targeted%20by%20hackers%20in%20major%20commercial%20litigations%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Hastings%2C%20now%20with%20the%20London%20firm%20Quillon%20Law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbramovich's%20representatives%20said%20the%20tycoon%20had%20no%20dealings%20with%20or%20knowledge%20of%20Mor%20or%20Appin%2C%20and%20that%20he%20had%20never%20engaged%20with%20hackers%20or%20hacked%20material%20of%20any%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20Appin's%20clients%20signed%20into%20My%20Commando%20using%20their%20real%20names.%20A%20prolific%20customer%20who%20didn't%20was%20someone%20using%20the%20alias%20%E2%80%9CJim%20H.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJim%20H%20assigned%20the%20Appin%20hackers%20more%20than%2030%20targets%20in%202011%20and%202012%2C%20including%20a%20Rwandan%20dissident%20and%20the%20wife%20of%20another%20wealthy%20Russian%20who%20was%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20divorce%2C%20the%20logs%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20Jim%20H's%20most%20sensitive%20requests%3A%20hacking%20Kristi%20Rogers%2C%20wife%20of%20Representative%20Mike%20Rogers%2C%20then-Chairman%20of%20the%20U.S.%20House%20Intelligence%20Committee.%20The%20Michigan%20Republican%20served%20in%20Congress%20from%202001%20until%20his%20retirement%20in%202015%3B%20he's%20currently%20running%20for%20U.S.%20Senate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202012%2C%20Kristi%20Rogers%20was%20an%20executive%20at%20Aegis%2C%20a%20London-based%20security%20company.%20Jim%20H%20told%20the%20hackers%20that%20Aegis%20competed%20with%20his%20client%2C%20another%20security%20contractor%20called%20Global%20Security%2C%20an%20apparent%20reference%20to%20Virginia-based%20Global%20Integrated%20Security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECracking%20Rogers'%20corporate%20email%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctop%20priority%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jim%20H%20told%20the%20hackers.%20He%20claimed%20that%20her%20company%20was%20trying%20to%20undermine%20Global's%20bid%20for%20a%20%24480%20million%20U.S.%20Army%20Corps%20of%20Engineers%20contract%20to%20provide%20security%20for%20Afghanistan's%20reconstruction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJim%20H%20said%20he%20needed%20dirt%20on%20Aegis%20to%20sully%20its%20reputation%2C%20and%20he%20suggested%20a%20way%20to%20trick%20Rogers%20into%20opening%20a%20malicious%20link.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20could%20send%20an%20invitation%20to%20an%20event%20organised%20by%20the%20Rotary%20Club%20or%20a%20gala%20dinner%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%2C%20according%20to%20the%20logs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShortly%20thereafter%2C%20Appin%20reported%20back%20that%20it%20had%20successfully%20broken%20into%20Aegis'%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20could%20not%20verify%20whether%20Rogers'%20account%20was%20ultimately%20compromised.%20Global%20eventually%20won%20the%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERogers%2C%20who%20left%20Aegis%20in%20late%202012%2C%20told%20Reuters%20she%20was%20outraged%20to%20learn%20of%20the%20hacking%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20emails%20were%20stolen%3B%20now%20he's%20exposing%20the%20hack-and-leak%20industry%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20WSJ%20reporter%20says%20law%20firm%20used%20Indian%20hackers%20to%20sabotage%20his%20career%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20gives%20me%20goosebumps%20right%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20angers%20me%20that%20people%20are%20so%20cavalier%20with%20other%20people's%20reputations%20and%20their%20lives.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20was%20unable%20to%20determine%20Jim%20H's%20identity%20or%20whether%20he%20was%20telling%20the%20truth%20when%20he%20said%20Global%20was%20his%20client.%20Messages%20sent%20to%20Jim%20H's%20old%20email%20account%20were%20returned%20as%20undeliverable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobal%20Integrated%20Security's%20website%20is%20inoperative%2C%20and%20corporate%20records%20show%20its%20Virginia%20branch%20is%20inactive.%20Damian%20Perl%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Britain's%20Global%20Strategies%20Group%20%E2%80%93%20Global%20Integrated%20Security's%20former%20parent%20company%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cvehemently%E2%80%9D%20denies%20any%20allegations%20of%20wrongdoing%2C%20his%20family%20office%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20Corps%20of%20Engineers%20confirmed%20that%20Aegis%20had%20protested%20Global's%20contract%2C%20but%20said%20it%20could%20offer%20no%20further%20comment.%20Canadian%20security%20company%20GardaWorld%2C%20which%20acquired%20Aegis%20in%202015%2C%20said%20it%20had%20no%20information%20on%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20My%20Commando%20logs%20also%20shine%20new%20light%20on%20the%20Shinnecock%20casino%20scandal.%20In%20January%202012%2C%20a%20New%20York%20private%20eye%20named%20Steven%20Santarpia%20ordered%20the%20hack%20of%20tribal%20member%20Chuck%20Randall%2C%20whose%20leaked%20emails%20sparked%20chaos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20days%2C%20an%20Appin%20hacker%20reported%20to%20Santarpia%20that%20he%20had%20hit%20pay%20dirt%2C%20according%20to%20the%20logs%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20got%20success%20in%20investigating%20Chuck%40shinnecock.org.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CExcellent%2C%E2%80%9D%20Santarpia%20replied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESantarpia%20didn't%20respond%20to%20repeated%20messages%20sent%20by%20Reuters%20over%20several%20months%2C%20and%20he%20declined%20comment%20when%20a%20reporter%20approached%20him%20outside%20his%20Long%20Island%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOperations%20like%20Jim%20H's%20or%20Santarpia's%20were%20aimed%20at%20only%20three%20or%20four%20email%20accounts%20at%20a%20time.%20But%20Appin%20had%20greater%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EG%C3%B3mez%2C%20the%20Dominican%20publisher%2C%20ordered%20break-in%20attempts%20aimed%20at%20the%20email%20accounts%20of%20more%20than%20200%20high-profile%20Dominicans%2C%20the%20logs%20show.%20Among%20them%20was%20an%20account%20belonging%20to%20then-President%20Leonel%20Fern%C3%A1ndez%2C%20a%20frequent%20target%20of%20G%C3%B3mez's%20reporting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EG%C3%B3mez's%20hacking%20requests%20preceded%20several%20stories%20alleging%20government%20corruption%20that%20his%20paper%20published%20before%20it%20was%20raided%20by%20Dominican%20authorities%20in%20February%202012.%20G%C3%B3mez%20eventually%20shut%20it%20down%20amidst%20mounting%20official%20scrutiny%20of%20the%20hacking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20very%20active%20in%20requesting%20emails%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20Reuters%2C%20adding%20that%20those%20days%20are%20firmly%20%E2%80%9Cin%20my%20past.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFern%C3%A1ndez%20did%20not%20return%20messages%20seeking%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELawyers%20for%20Rajat%20Khare%20said%20he%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20know%E2%80%9D%20G%C3%B3mez%2C%20Santarpia%2C%20Mor%20or%20Halevi%20and%20%E2%80%9Chas%20no%20knowledge%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20My%20Commando%20dashboard%20%E2%80%9Cor%20anything%20similar.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ability%20to%20target%20heads%20of%20state%20was%20an%20improbable%20amount%20of%20power%20for%20a%20company%20that%20only%20a%20few%20years%20earlier%20had%20been%20teaching%20college%20kids%20to%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EApproaching%20infinity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajat%20Khare%20was%20a%2020-year-old%20computer%20science%20major%20when%20he%20and%20his%20friends%20came%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20for%20Appin%20over%20chicken%20pizza%20at%20a%20Domino's%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajat%20Khare%20at%20a%20party%20in%20New%20Delhi%20in%20or%20around%202007.%20He%20hatched%20the%20idea%20for%20Appin%20with%20some%20school%20chums%20back%20in%202003.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20December%202003.%20Khare%20had%20joined%20his%20high%20school%20buddies%20to%20catch%20up%20and%20bemoan%20the%20state%20of%20India's%20universities%2C%20which%20they%20thought%20weren't%20preparing%20students%20for%20the%20professional%20world.%20When%20one%20suggested%20organizing%20technology%20training%20workshops%20to%20supplement%20undergraduates'%20education%2C%20people%20present%20at%20the%20meal%20said%20Khare%20jumped%20on%20the%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLet's%20give%20the%20students%20what%20they%20want%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20quoted%20himself%20telling%20the%20group%20in%20a%20book%20on%20entrepreneurship%20he%20co-wrote%20years%20later.%20%E2%80%9CLet's%20start%20something%20that%20will%20not%20only%20change%20their%20lives%2C%20but%20our%20lives%20too%20%E2%80%A6%20forever.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Domino's%20meeting%2C%20Khare%20and%20his%20friends%20came%20up%20with%20the%20name%20Appin%20%E2%80%93%20short%20for%20%E2%80%9CApproaching%20infinity%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20and%20launched%20their%20first%20classes%20on%20computer%20programming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20right%20idea%20at%20the%20right%20time.%20India's%20IT%20outsourcing%20boom%20had%20created%20voracious%20demand%20for%20tech%20talent.%20Appin%20franchises%20would%20soon%20sprout%20across%20India%2C%20offering%20not%20just%20programming%20lessons%20but%20also%20courses%20on%20robotics%20and%20cybersecurity%2C%20nicknamed%20%E2%80%9Cethical%20hacking.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202005%2C%20the%20company%20had%20an%20office%20in%20western%20New%20Delhi.%20Rajat%20had%20been%20joined%20by%20his%20older%20brother%2C%20Anuj%2C%20a%20motivational%20speaker%20who%20returned%20to%20India%20after%20a%20stint%20running%20a%20startup%20in%20Texas.%20As%20other%20members%20of%20the%20Domino's%20group%20stepped%20away%2C%20the%20Khare%20brothers%20took%20charge%20of%20the%20fast-growing%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cybersecurity%20classes%20proved%20especially%20popular.%20By%202007%2C%20Appin%20opened%20a%20digital%20security%20consultancy%20helping%20Indian%20organizations%20protect%20themselves%20online%2C%20according%20to%20a%20draft%20pitch%20deck%20intended%20for%20potential%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20soon%20drew%20the%20attention%20of%20Indian%20government%20officials%20who%20were%20still%20feeling%20their%20way%20through%20intelligence%20work%20in%20the%20internet%20age.%20To%20help%20the%20officials%20break%20into%20computers%20and%20emails%2C%20Appin%20set%20up%20a%20team%20of%20hackers%20out%20of%20a%20subsidiary%20called%20Appin%20Software%20Security%20Pvt.%20Ltd.%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Appin%20Security%20Group%2C%20according%20to%20a%20former%20executive%2C%20company%20communications%2C%20an%20ex-senior%20Indian%20intelligence%20figure%20and%20promotional%20documents%20seen%20by%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spying%20was%20a%20secret%20within%20the%20wider%20company.%20Some%20early%20Appin%20employees%20signed%20nondisclosure%20agreements%20before%20being%20shipped%20off%20to%20military-controlled%20safe%20houses%20where%20they%20worked%20out%20of%20sight%20from%20their%20colleagues%2C%20according%20to%20another%20former%20executive%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20and%20three%20hackers%20who%20spent%20time%20in%20the%20safe%20houses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20hackers%20recalled%20being%20only%2022%20years%20old%20when%20he%20broke%20into%20the%20inboxes%20of%20Khalistani%20separatists%20%E2%80%93%20Sikh%20militants%20fighting%20to%20carve%20an%20independent%20homeland%20out%20of%20India's%20Punjab%20province%20%E2%80%93%20and%20delivering%20the%20trove%20to%20his%20handlers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20experience%20of%20a%20lifetime%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20recalling%20how%20proud%20he%20was%20to%20be%20contributing%20to%20India's%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnuj%20Khare%20walks%20on%20a%20bed%20of%20broken%20glass%20on%20a%20rooftop%20in%20New%20Delhi%20in%20or%20around%202007.%20%C2%A0A%20former%20motivational%20speaker%2C%20he%20ran%20Appin%20together%20with%20his%20brother%20Rajat%20as%20it%20grew%20from%20a%20modest%20Indian%20education%20company%20into%20a%20hub%20for%20outsourced%20cyberespionage%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Appin's%20primary%20targets%20was%20Pakistan%2C%20according%20to%20interviews%20with%20former%20insiders%2C%20company%20emails%2C%20and%20stolen%20passwords%20and%20key%20logs%20of%20Pakistani%20officials%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters.%20The%20hackers%20created%20fake%20dating%20websites%20designed%20to%20ensnare%20Pakistani%20military%20officers%2C%20two%20of%20the%20insiders%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20early%20mission%2C%20dubbed%20Operation%20Rainbow%2C%20involved%20penetrating%20Chinese%20military%20computers%20and%20stealing%20information%20about%20missiles%20and%20radar%2C%20according%20to%20an%20undated%20Appin%20memo.%20The%20memo%20said%20the%20company's%20hackers%20compromised%20several%20Chinese%20officials%3B%20Reuters%20was%20unable%20to%20confirm%20the%20alleged%20intrusions%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20early%20operations%20led%20to%20more%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20Appin%20was%20working%20with%20the%20Research%20%26amp%3B%20Analysis%20Wing%20(RAW)%2C%20India's%20external%20intelligence%20service%3B%20and%20the%20Intelligence%20Bureau%2C%20the%20country's%20domestic%20spy%20agency%2C%20according%20to%20the%20two%20former%20executives%2C%20one%20former%20Appin%20hacker%20and%20a%20former%20senior%20Indian%20intelligence%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDetailed%20messages%20from%20Reuters%20seeking%20comment%20from%20the%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20and%20RAW%2C%20sent%20via%20India's%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20and%20its%20Cabinet%20Secretariat%2C%20respectively%2C%20were%20not%20returned.%20India's%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20did%20not%20return%20messages%20about%20the%20hacking.%20The%20Pakistani%20foreign%20affairs%20ministry%20did%20not%20return%20messages.%20China's%20foreign%20ministry%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20it%20was%20unaware%20of%20the%20hacking%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202008%2C%20Appin%20was%20claiming%20it%20offered%20a%20%E2%80%9Cone%20stop%20interception%20solution%E2%80%9D%20for%20government%20clients%2C%20according%20to%20one%20company%20presentation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompany%20executives%20marketed%20software%20for%20the%20analysis%20of%20call%20record%20data%E2%80%93%20the%20who%2C%20what%2C%20when%20of%20phone%20calls%20monitored%20by%20spy%20agencies%20and%20law%20enforcement%20%E2%80%93%20and%20discussed%20the%20importation%20of%20Israeli%20cell%20phone%20interception%20devices%2C%20Appin%20emails%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20Appin%20boasted%20to%20prospective%20customers%20that%20it%20was%20serving%20India's%20military%2C%20its%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20and%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%2C%20an%20Indian%20agency%20roughly%20equivalent%20to%20America's%20Federal%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(FBI)%2C%20emails%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppin's%20solutions%20%E2%80%9Care%20being%20used%20by%20various%20elite%20intelligence%20agencies%20in%20government%20to%20monitor%20hostile%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20one%20pitch%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20and%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20didn't%20return%20detailed%20messages%20seeking%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompany%20revenues%20in%20the%20fiscal%20year%20ending%20in%202009%20were%20estimated%20at%20nearly%20%241%20million%2C%20with%20profit%20after%20tax%20pegged%20at%20about%20%24170%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20the%20draft%20pitch%20deck%20aimed%20at%20potential%20investors.%20The%20deck%20projected%20that%20figure%20would%20multiply%20almost%20tenfold%20over%20the%20next%2036%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Appin%20had%20hit%20a%20speed%20bump.%20The%20two%20former%20executives%2C%20one%20of%20the%20former%20hackers%2C%20and%20the%20former%20Indian%20intelligence%20official%20said%20the%20company%20earned%20extra%20money%20by%20quietly%20taking%20material%20it%20hacked%20for%20one%20Indian%20agency%20and%20reselling%20it%20to%20another.%20This%20double%20dipping%20was%20eventually%20discovered%2C%20the%20people%20said%2C%20and%20several%20enraged%20spy%20agency%20clients%20canceled%20their%20contracts%20with%20Appin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20intelligence%20work%20drying%20up%2C%20Appin%20pivoted%20to%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20the%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Fucking%20with%20the%20wrong%20people'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20influx%20of%20Western%20clients%20brought%20new%20revenue%20%E2%80%93%20and%20new%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerican%20and%20Swiss%20law%20enforcement%20documents%2C%20including%20emails%20and%20investigative%20reports%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters%2C%20reveal%20how%20Appin%20got%20caught%20hacking%20as%20it%20fulfilled%20its%20customers'%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20early%20example%20was%20the%20compromise%20of%20prominent%20Zurich-based%20communications%20consultant%20Peter%20Hargitay%2C%20who%20had%20served%20as%20an%20advisor%20to%20Australia's%20football%20federation.%20He%20and%20his%20filmmaker%20son%20Stevie%20detected%20the%20intrusion%20and%20filed%20a%20Swiss%20criminal%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20weeks%2C%20an%20expert%20they%20hired%20traced%20the%20hack%20to%20a%20server%20near%20the%20Zurich%20airport%2C%20according%20to%20the%20law%20enforcement%20documents.%20Billing%20records%20tied%20to%20the%20server%20listed%20Rajat%20Khare%20as%20the%20client.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFather%20and%20son%20had%20come%20off%20a%20failed%20bid%20to%20bring%20the%202022%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%20to%20Australia%20and%20were%20in%20no%20mood%20to%20let%20the%20hack%20slide%2C%20according%20to%20emails%20provided%20by%20an%20independent%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20March%202012%20message%20to%20his%20father%2C%20Stevie%20said%20he%20had%20spoken%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20an%20Appin%20employee%20who%20was%20clearly%20rattled%20by%20the%20exchange.%20%E2%80%9CI%20told%20him%20in%20no%20uncertain%20terms%20that%20they%20are%20fucking%20with%20the%20wrong%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20Stevie%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajat%20Khare%20called%20Stevie%20the%20same%20day%20to%20try%20to%20smooth%20things%20over%2C%20saying%20he%20%E2%80%9Cwants%20to%20cooperate%20%E2%80%98100%25%2C'%E2%80%9D%20Stevie%20wrote.%20The%20emails%20show%20that%20an%20Appin%20employee%20later%20told%20Stevie%20the%20hack%20was%20ordered%20by%20a%20U.S.%20private%20investigator%3B%20contact%20fell%20off%20as%20the%20Hargitays%20pushed%20for%20more%20information%20about%20who%20was%20ultimately%20behind%20the%20spying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20don't%20know%20who%20his%20client%20was%2C%E2%80%9D%20Peter%20Hargitay%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhare's%20lawyers%20told%20Reuters%20he%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20know%E2%80%9D%20the%20Hargitays.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20later%2C%20Appin%20was%20implicated%20in%20another%20incident%2C%20this%20time%20in%20India.%20Cybersecurity%20consultant%20K.%20K.%20Mookhey%20told%20a%20conference%20near%20New%20Delhi%20that%20he%20had%20tied%20an%20attempted%20hack%20against%20one%20of%20his%20clients%20to%20the%20firm.%20In%20a%20report%20published%20in%202013%2C%20Mookhey%20wrote%20that%20the%20link%20to%20Appin%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20concrete.%E2%80%9D%20But%20he%20told%20Reuters%20he%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Covercautious%E2%80%9D%20in%20choosing%20those%20words%20and%20that%20the%20evidence%2C%20including%20Appin%20documentation%20inadvertently%20left%20on%20the%20hackers'%20servers%2C%20made%20it%20obvious%20they%20were%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20link%20was%20actually%20pretty%20clear%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppin's%20name%20had%20popped%20up%20earlier%20that%20year%20in%20Norway.%20In%20February%202013%2C%20technicians%20at%20telecommunications%20company%20Telenor%20discovered%20that%20hackers%20had%20stolen%20as%20many%20as%2066%2C000%20emails%20from%20the%20company's%20chief%20executive%2C%20two%20personal%20assistants%20and%20a%20senior%20lawyer%20at%20the%20firm%2C%20according%20to%20Norwegian%20law%20enforcement%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20months%20later%2C%20Oslo-based%20cybersecurity%20firm%20Norman%20Shark%20%E2%80%93%20which%20had%20launched%20its%20own%20independent%20investigation%20into%20the%20Telenor%20hack%20%E2%80%93%20publicly%20linked%20the%20intrusion%20to%20Appin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETelenor's%20headquarters%20in%20Fornebu%2C%20Norway.%20Hackers%20stole%2066%2C000%20emails%20from%20the%20telecom%20firm%20in%202013%2C%20an%20incident%20the%20company%20described%20as%20%E2%80%9Cindustrial%20espionage.%E2%80%9D%20REUTERS%2FInts%20Kalnins%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Oslo%20headquarters%20of%20Kripos%2C%20Norway's%20national%20criminal%20police%20service.%20Kripos%20traced%20the%20Telenor%20hack%20to%20India%2C%20according%20to%20law%20enforcement%20files%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters.%20But%20the%20investigation%20ran%20aground%20and%20was%20eventually%20closed%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorman%20Shark%20stopped%20short%20of%20directly%20blaming%20the%20company%2C%20saying%20only%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20seems%20to%20be%20some%20connection%E2%80%9D%20between%20Appin%20and%20the%20Telenor%20hackers.%20One%20of%20the%20report's%20coauthors%2C%20security%20researcher%20Jonathan%20Camp%2C%20told%20Reuters%20that%20Norman%20Shark%20had%20softened%20the%20report's%20language%20to%20avoid%20legal%20trouble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECamp%20said%20he%20and%20his%20colleagues%20privately%20were%20confident%20that%20Appin%20was%20behind%20the%20hacking%2C%20citing%20an%20unusually%20large%20number%20of%20digital%20clues%20pointing%20to%20the%20company%2C%20including%20multiple%20malicious%20websites%20registered%20under%20the%20Appin%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20no%20doubt%20in%20our%20minds%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalifornia-based%20tech%20firm%20Broadcom%2C%20which%20absorbed%20Norman%20Shark%20following%20a%20series%20of%20acquisitions%2C%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20seeking%20comment.%20Telenor%20confirmed%20it%20had%20been%20the%20victim%20of%20%E2%80%9Cindustrial%20espionage%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20it%20reported%20to%20police%20at%20the%20time.%20It%20declined%20further%20comment.%20The%20motive%20behind%20the%20hacking%20has%20never%20been%20made%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppin%20denied%20all%20wrongdoing%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20Camp's%20report%2C%20and%20the%20Khares'%20lawyers%20still%20insist%20the%20research%20didn't%20implicate%20the%20company.%20Nevertheless%2C%20Appin%20came%20under%20increasing%20scrutiny%20in%20the%20years%20that%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorway%20was%20one%20of%20at%20least%20four%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20along%20with%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Switzerland%20and%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%20%E2%80%93%20that%20had%20opened%20investigations%20into%20Appin.%20Some%20began%20comparing%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20undated%20written%20exchange%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters%2C%20FBI%20official%20Dan%20Brady%20told%20Swiss%20prosecutor%20Sandra%20Schweingruber%20that%20U.S.%20officials%20looking%20into%20the%20hack%20of%20the%20Shinnecock%20tribe%20on%20Long%20Island%20had%20%E2%80%9Caccumulated%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20data%20identifying%20other%20victims.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESchweingruber%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%20Reuters%20was%20unable%20to%20reach%20Brady.%20The%20FBI%20declined%20to%20answer%20a%20list%20of%20questions%20about%20its%20investigation%20into%20Appin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20note%20to%20Schweingruber%2C%20Brady%20said%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20link%20in%20our%20respective%20cases%20is%20that%20I%20believe%20we%20have%20the%20same%20ultimate%20perpetrator.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20he%20added%2C%20in%20parentheses%3A%20%E2%80%9CAppin.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ELost%20leads%2C%20lasting%20pain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20multinational%20investigations%20into%20Appin%20each%20carried%20on%20for%20years%20before%20petering%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJochi%20G%C3%B3mez%2C%20the%20Dominican%20newspaper%20publisher%2C%20was%20formally%20accused%20of%20working%20with%20Rajat%20Khare%20to%20hack%20emails%20following%20the%202012%20raid%20on%20his%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20case%20never%20went%20to%20trial%3B%20it%20was%20quashed%20on%20procedural%20grounds%20in%202013%2C%20a%20decision%20reaffirmed%20by%20the%20country's%20highest%20court%20the%20following%20year.%20Dominican%20prosecutors%20described%20Khare%20as%20a%20member%20of%20G%C3%B3mez's%20%E2%80%9Cinternational%20criminal%20network.%E2%80%9D%20But%20one%20of%20the%20judges%20involved%20dismissed%20the%20idea%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctheory.%E2%80%9D%20Khare%20was%20never%20charged%20in%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDominican%20entrepreneur%20Jochi%20G%C3%B3mez%20in%20Punta%20Cana%2C%20Dominican%20Republic%20in%20January%202023.%20G%C3%B3mez%20hired%20Appin%20to%20dig%20up%20dirt%20on%20the%20country's%20elite%20for%20his%20now-defunct%20digital%20newspaper.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDominican%20judiciary%20officials%20didn't%20return%20messages%20seeking%20comment%20about%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20Reuters%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20G%C3%B3mez%20acknowledged%20hiring%20Khare%20for%20surveillance%2C%20saying%20he%20had%20been%20hunting%20for%20evidence%20of%20corruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20did%20it%20for%20journalism%2C%E2%80%9D%20G%C3%B3mez%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIs%20it%20lawful%20or%20not%3F%20That's%20another%20story.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorway's%20investigation%20into%20the%20Telenor%20hack%20led%20to%20four%20internet%20protocol%20addresses%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20according%20to%20the%20law%20enforcement%20files%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters.%20In%20an%20undated%20email%20sent%20to%20the%20FBI%2C%20the%20Swiss%20prosecutor%20Schweingruber%20said%20the%20Norwegians%20had%20gone%20further%20still.%20%E2%80%9CTheir%20investigation%20leads%20also%20to%20Appin%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20inquiry%20similarly%20ran%20aground.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Norway's%20National%20Criminal%20Investigation%20Service%20confirmed%20to%20Reuters%20that%20the%20case%20was%20closed%20in%20June%202016%20%E2%80%9Ctaking%20into%20consideration%20the%20chances%20of%20obtaining%20further%20evidence%20and%20information%20through%20further%20investigation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwiss%20authorities%20also%20implicated%20Appin%20in%20the%20case%20of%20PR%20consultant%20Peter%20Hargitay%2C%20according%20to%20the%20files.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20email%20to%20the%20FBI%2C%20Schweingruber%20said%20the%20Swiss%20investigation%20%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20nicknamed%20%E2%80%9CTandoori%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20had%20found%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Indian%20company%20Appin%20Security%20Group%20as%20well%20as%20their%20CEO%20Rajat%20Khare%20are%20involved%20in%20this%20case.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20files%20show%20Swiss%20authorities%20rebuffed%20the%20Hargitays'%20request%20to%20have%20Khare%20quizzed%20about%20the%20hack.%20In%20a%20message%20to%20the%20Hargitays%20sent%20in%20September%202020%2C%20Schweingruber's%20successor%2C%20Anna%20Carter%2C%20said%20she%20was%20discontinuing%20the%20case%20%E2%80%9Cdue%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20further%20promising%20investigative%20approaches.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwiss%20prosecutors%20confirmed%20that%20the%20investigation%20was%20closed%2C%20but%20wouldn't%20elaborate.%20Peter%20Hargitay%20told%20Reuters%20that%20the%20prosecutors'%20decision%20%E2%80%9Cremains%20a%20mystery%20to%20us%20to%20this%20day.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20can%20do%20this%20from%20across%20the%20world.%20The%20penalties%20and%20the%20laws%20have%20to%20catch%20up.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHacking%20victim%20Chuck%20Randall%20of%20the%20Shinnecock%20Nation%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20U.S.%20cybercrime%20prosecutor%20Mark%20Califano%20told%20Reuters%20that%20cracking%20international%20hacking%20cases%20is%20%E2%80%9Creally%20very%20hard.%E2%80%9D%20But%20he%20said%20it%20was%20still%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20disconcerting%E2%80%9D%20that%20Appin's%20hackers%20were%20%E2%80%9Cso%20successful%20in%20evading%20law%20enforcement%20despite%20apparently%20significant%20effort%20to%20try%20to%20track%20them%20down%20%E2%80%93%20and%20some%20very%20good%20evidence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajat%20Khare's%20lawyers%20said%20their%20client%20had%20never%20been%20charged%20with%20hacking%20%E2%80%9Cby%20any%20police%2C%20investigative%2C%20regulatory%2C%20or%20charging%20authority.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20was%20unable%20to%20establish%20whether%20Appin%20was%20ever%20investigated%20in%20its%20native%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EK.%20K.%20Mookhey%2C%20the%20cybersecurity%20consultant%20whose%20client%20was%20targeted%20by%20Appin%2C%20said%20he%20alerted%20India's%20cyber%20response%20agency%2C%20CERT-In%2C%20in%202013%2C%20but%20never%20heard%20back.%20CERT-In%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajat%20Khare%20has%20come%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Indian%20government%20on%20a%20separate%20matter%3A%20A%202021%20complaint%20filed%20with%20the%20country's%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20accused%20Khare%20of%20being%20one%20of%20at%20least%20eight%20people%20who%20embezzled%20roughly%208.06%20billion%20rupees%20(%2497%20million)%20lent%20to%20the%20Indian%20education%20company%20Educomp%2C%20where%20he%20had%20previously%20served%20as%20a%20director.%20There%20is%20no%20indication%20that%20the%20case%20is%20related%20to%20hacking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20was%20filed%20by%20a%20senior%20official%20at%20the%20country's%20biggest%20lender%2C%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India.%20Reuters%20could%20not%20determine%20the%20case's%20status.%20The%20State%20Bank%2C%20the%20CBI%20and%20Educomp%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%20Khare's%20lawyers%20said%20he%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Ccleared%E2%80%9D%20by%20Educomp's%20management.%20They%20didn't%20provide%20evidence%20and%20said%20they%20could%20not%20offer%20details%20on%20the%20CBI%20probe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EU.S.%20intelligence%20agencies%20have%20known%20about%20Appin's%20capabilities%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20according%20to%20three%20former%20American%20security%20officials%20and%20law%20enforcement%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Security%20Agency%20(NSA)%2C%20which%20spies%20on%20foreigners%20for%20the%20U.S.%20government%2C%20began%20surveilling%20the%20company%20after%20watching%20it%20hack%20%E2%80%9Chigh%20value%E2%80%9D%20Pakistani%20officials%20around%202009%2C%20one%20of%20the%20sources%20said.%20An%20NSA%20spokesperson%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20former%20U.S.%20security%20official%20said%20Rajat%20Khare%20was%20of%20such%20interest%20that%20the%20FBI%20tracked%20his%20travel%20and%20communications.%20The%20law%20enforcement%20case%20files%20also%20show%20that%20the%20FBI%20told%20its%20Swiss%20counterparts%20that%20it%20had%20%E2%80%9Ca%20confidential%20human%20source%20who%20has%20the%20capacity%20to%20report%20on%20Appin%20Security%20matters.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajat%20Khare's%20lawyers%20said%20the%20notion%20that%20he%20had%20been%20investigated%20by%20the%20FBI%20or%20any%20other%20such%20law%20enforcement%20body%20was%20%E2%80%9Cabsurd.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bureau's%20investigation%20into%20the%20Appin%20hack%20that%20sparked%20turmoil%20within%20the%20Shinnecock%20Nation%20did%20yield%20two%20convictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20came%20in%202016%2C%20when%20a%20Shinnecock%20tribal%20official%20named%20Karen%20Hunter%20pleaded%20guilty%20at%20a%20federal%20court%20in%20the%20Long%20Island%20town%20of%20Islip%20to%20unlawfully%20accessing%20the%20email%20account%20of%20her%20fellow%20Shinnecock%20tribal%20member%20Chuck%20Randall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20van%20drives%20past%20a%20%E2%80%9CNo%20Trespassing%E2%80%9D%20sign%20at%20the%20border%20of%20Shinnecock%20Indian%20Nation%20Territory%20on%20Long%20Island%2C%20New%20York.%20In%202012%2C%20the%20Shinnecocks%20were%20thrown%20into%20turmoil%20by%20a%20hack-and-leak%20operation%20that%20led%20to%20the%20removal%20of%20several%20members%20from%20tribal%20government%20and%20sparked%20an%20FBI%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20filings%2C%20which%20were%20partially%20sealed%2C%20show%20that%20Hunter%20got%20probation.%20It%20was%20not%20until%20several%20years%20later%20that%20Steven%20Santarpia%2C%20the%20private%20eye%2C%20said%20he%20had%20been%20hired%20by%20Hunter%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESantarpia%20was%20the%20second%20to%20be%20convicted.%20He%20received%20probation%20from%20the%20same%20court%20in%20Islip%20in%202020%20after%20pleading%20guilty%20to%20a%20single%20count%20of%20computer%20hacking%2C%20saying%20in%20an%20affidavit%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters%20that%20he%20hired%20Appin%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20email%20heist.%20Most%20of%20the%20filings%20in%20that%20case%2C%20which%20mask%20his%20identity%2C%20remain%20secret.%20No%20public%20mention%20of%20Appin%20was%20made%20in%20either%20his%20or%20Hunter's%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHunter%20did%20not%20return%20repeated%20messages%20from%20Reuters%20seeking%20comment.%20A%20reporter%20who%20visited%20Shinnecock%20Nation%20territory%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20interview%20her%20was%20intercepted%20by%20the%20tribe's%20chairman%2C%20Bryan%20Polite%2C%20and%20ordered%20off%20the%20reservation.%20Polite%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20the%20tribe's%20governing%20body%20was%20not%20interested%20in%20commenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERandall%20said%20he%20was%20baffled%20by%20the%20U.S.%20government's%20lack%20of%20action%20against%20Appin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20can%20do%20this%20from%20across%20the%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20penalties%20and%20the%20laws%20have%20to%20catch%20up.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpoke%20with%20the%20client%20today.%20Her%20husband%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20big%20sex%20addict.%20She%20found%20out%20he%20goes%20to%20swinger%20clubs.%20She%20believes%20these%202%20mail%20addresses.%20%5Bemail%20addresses%20redacted%5D%2C%20will%20be%20the%20addresses%20we%20will%20find%20stuff%20about%20him%20cheating.%20She%20doesn't%20think%20the%20aol%20address%20will%20have%20much%20information%20about%20his%20cheating.%20So%20if%20we%20can%20get%20in%20those%202%20email%20addresses%2C%20we%20should%20find%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20Island%20private%20detective%20Steven%20Santarpia%20on%20May%2010%2C%202011%2C%20chats%20with%20Appin%20employees%20about%20hacking%20a%20man%20whose%20wife%20suspects%20infidelity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpoke%20with%20the%20client%20today.%20Her%20husband%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20big%20sex%20addict.%20She%20found%20out%20he%20goes%20to%20swinger%20clubs.%20She%20believes%20these%202%20mail%20addresses.%20%5Bemail%20addresses%20redacted%5D%2C%20will%20be%20the%20addresses%20we%20will%20find%20stuff%20about%20him%20cheating.%20She%20doesn't%20think%20the%20aol%20address%20will%20have%20much%20information%20about%20his%20cheating.%20So%20if%20we%20can%20get%20in%20those%202%20email%20addresses%2C%20we%20should%20find%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20Island%20private%20detective%20Steven%20Santarpia%20on%20May%2010%2C%202011%2C%20chats%20with%20Appin%20employees%20about%20hacking%20a%20man%20whose%20wife%20suspects%20infidelity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20California%20private%20eye%20asks%20Appin%20on%20Nov.%2016%2C%202011%2C%20for%20advice%20on%20how%20to%20move%20undetected%20through%20a%20woman's%20hacked%20email%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Godfather%20for%20all%20hackers'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppin's%20legacy%20still%20lingers%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20after%20the%20Shinnecock%20hack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20web%20presence%20faded%20in%20the%20months%20following%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20Norman%20Shark%20report%20in%202013%2C%20internet%20archives%20show.%20Eight%20former%20employees%20say%20their%20old%20managers%20told%20them%20to%20delete%20references%20to%20Appin%20from%20their%20public%20profiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20former%20holding%20company%2C%20Appin%20Technology%2C%20changed%20its%20name%20three%20times%2C%20finally%20settling%20on%20Sunkissed%20Organic%20Farms%20in%202017%2C%20records%20filed%20with%20India's%20Ministry%20of%20Corporate%20Affairs%20show.%20Its%20subsidiaries%20also%20underwent%20rebrandings%3A%20Appin%20Software%20Security%2C%20the%20arm%20which%20billed%20private%20eyes%20for%20the%20hacking%20work%2C%20became%20Adaptive%20Control%20Security%20Global%20Corporate%2C%20or%20ACSG%2C%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajat%20Khare's%20lawyers%20say%20he%20left%20Appin%20Technology%20in%20December%202012%2C%20a%20move%20that%20%E2%80%9Cofficially%20and%20immediately%20separated%20him%20from%20all%20Appin%20entities.%E2%80%9D%20They%20produced%20two%20letters%20they%20said%20showed%20those%20resignations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20Khare's%20signature%20is%20on%20several%20Appin%20corporate%20filings%20dating%20to%202013%20and%202014%3B%20and%20shareholder%20data%20shows%20he%20maintained%20a%20stake%20in%20Appin%20Technology%20for%20several%20years%20past%202012.%20According%20to%20Indian%20corporate%20records%2C%20Khare%20%E2%80%93%20who%20is%20now%20a%20Switzerland-based%20investor%20%E2%80%93%20resigned%20as%20director%20of%20the%20company%20once%20known%20as%20Appin%20Technology%20only%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20family%20still%20controlled%20the%20companies%20as%20recently%20as%20last%20year.%20Rajat's%20brother%2C%20Anuj%2C%20and%20their%20father%2C%20Vijay%20Kumar%2C%20are%20majority%20owners%20of%20Sunkissed%20Organic%20Farms%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20owns%20ACSG%20and%20at%20least%20two%20other%20firms%20founded%20under%20the%20Appin%20name%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20available%20financial%20data%20disclosed%20to%20the%20corporate%20affairs%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20exchange%20of%20messages%20over%20WhatsApp%20this%20week%2C%20ACSG%20company%20secretary%20Deepak%20Kumar%20confirmed%20that%20his%20firm%20was%20once%20known%20as%20Appin%20and%20described%20Rajat%20Khare%20as%20the%20corporate%20group's%20%E2%80%9Cowner.%E2%80%9D%20The%20following%20day%2C%20he%20said%20he%20would%20no%20longer%20reply%20to%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnuj%20Khare's%20lawyer%2C%20Kumar%20%26amp%3B%20Kumar%20Advocates%2C%20said%20questions%20about%20his%20client's%20financial%20dealings%20were%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20relevant.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Khare%20brothers'%20father%2C%20Vijay%20Kumar%2C%20did%20not%20return%20repeated%20messages%20seeking%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20its%20website%2C%20ACSG%20describes%20itself%20as%20a%20critical%20infrastructure%20protection%20company%20that%20caters%20to%20government%20clients.%20Employee%20resumes%20posted%20to%20job%20sites%20say%20the%20company%20carries%20out%20%E2%80%9Clawful%20interception%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Coffensive%20security%2C%E2%80%9D%20industry%20terms%20for%20digital%20surveillance%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2050%20current%20and%20former%20ACSG%20employees%20reached%20by%20Reuters%20either%20did%20not%20respond%20or%20declined%20to%20comment%2C%20saying%20their%20work%20was%20confidential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20metro%20train%20moves%20past%20commercial%20buildings%20in%20the%20Netaji%20Subhash%20Place%20area%20of%20New%20Delhi.%20The%20neighborhood%20is%20a%20technology%20hotbed%20where%20Appin%20once%20operated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20found%20at%20least%20half%20a%20dozen%20other%20hack-for-hire%20firms%20in%20India%20that%20have%20adopted%20Appin's%20business%20model%20of%20serving%20private%20investigators%20and%20corporate%20lawyers.%20Some%20have%20run%20into%20trouble%20with%20American%20tech%20companies%20or%20been%20named%20in%20U.S.%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%20owner%20Meta%20Platforms%20identified%20CyberRoot%20Risk%20Advisory%2C%20a%20firm%20created%20by%20Appin%20alumni%2C%20as%20a%20mercenary%20spy%20company%20that%20used%20bogus%20accounts%20to%20trick%20people%20into%20clicking%20malicious%20links.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202022%2C%20CyberRoot%20and%20BellTroX%20InfoTech%20Services%2C%20another%20firm%20founded%20by%20a%20former%20Appin%20employee%2C%20were%20accused%20of%20hacking%20former%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reporter%20Jay%20Solomon%20and%20one%20of%20his%20key%20sources%2C%20according%20to%20lawsuits%20filed%20last%20year%20by%20each%20of%20the%20men%20in%20federal%20court%2C%20one%20in%20Washington%2C%20the%20other%20in%20New%20York.%20Solomon%20later%20settled%20his%20Washington%20case%20on%20undisclosed%20terms%3B%20the%20New%20York%20lawsuit%20filed%20by%20his%20source%20is%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202022%2C%20Google%20researchers%20linked%20hack-for-hire%20activity%20to%20another%20Indian%20company%20named%20Rebsec%20Solutions%2C%20which%20Google%20said%20%E2%80%9Copenly%20advertises%20corporate%20espionage.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERebsec's%20founder%2C%20Vishavdeep%20Singh%2C%20told%20Reuters%20he%20had%20worked%20for%20Appin%20and%20BellTroX%20but%20was%20never%20involved%20in%20hacking%2C%20and%20that%20Rebsec%20merely%20taught%20cybersecurity%20courses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECyberRoot%20said%20in%20a%20public%20statement%20issued%20last%20year%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Chas%20never%20engaged%20in%20illegal%20activities.%E2%80%9D%20It%20declined%20further%20commen